<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Ashley Benson made a typical coffee run on Friday. </p>

<p>And the former Pretty Little Liars actress flaunted an edgy black outfit for her outing in Los Angeles' Los Feliz neighborhood. </p>

<p>She covered up in a graphic sweatshirt and a face mask before heading out of the coffee ship. </p>

<p>Edgy: Ashley Benson flaunted an edgy black outfit for her outing in Los Angeles' Los Feliz neighborhood on Friday</p>

<p>The 30-year-old actress opted for black skinny jeans, that featured a rip above her knee. </p>

<p>She added a black crewneck sweatshirt and black Dr. Marten boots adding height to her look. </p>

<p>For some added touches, she wore a gold watch and layered gold necklaces. </p>

<p>Heading out: For some added touches, she wore a gold watch and layered gold necklaces as she left in her SUV</p>

<p>VOTE: Later in the day, the star took to social media to encourage her fans to vote </p>

<p>Ashley left her blonde hair down in wavy style and parted to the side as she left with iced coffee in hand. </p>

<p>Later in the day, the star took to social media to encourage her fans to vote. </p>

<p>Using a filter, her face was colorfully colored with hearts, smiley faces, the female gender symbol, flowers and a voting sticker.</p>

<p>'Vote!' was written across her forehead, while 'power to the people,' was near her hairline and 'BLM,' was plastered on her cheek. </p>

<p>Congratulations: On Tuesday, she shared a video of her her mother ringing a bell to mark the end of her cancer treatment (pictured in 2015)</p>

<p>Happy moment: Captioning the image, the star said that she's 'so proud' of her mother as she expressed her love for her </p>

<p>She held up a dainty gold necklace that read 'vote,' and she echoed the sentiment by writing the same word over the selfie. </p>

<p>On Tuesday, she shared a video of her her mother ringing a bell to mark the end of her cancer treatment. </p>

<p>Captioning the image, the star said that she's 'so proud' of her mother as she expressed her love for her. </p>

<p>Ashley penned: 'So happy for my mom finishing her last day of chemo. I love you.' </p>
